      "automation_source": "clawsweeper",
      "repair_reason": "Draft protected policy/runtime work needs maintainer architecture and security review after the narrow enablement blocker is fixed.; Needs attention: The diff introduces a trusted runtime policy gate, and the current enablement guard can silently leave that gate unenforced for the normal plugin-enabled setup.; Review finding: [P2] Honor plugin enablement for runtime policy — extensions/policy/src/runtime-tool-policy... (sha=db9afd9dd8486922c300c62284c2bdbc63698524)",
      "review_summary": "The PR adds a bundled policy plugin with tool metadata conformance checks, doctor lint integration, oc-path document APIs, policy attestations, and an optional trusted-tool runtime gate.\n\nReproducibility: yes. source-reproducible. With plugins.entries.policy.enabled=true and plugins.entries.policy.config.runtimeToolPolicy=true but no config.enabled, the runtime evaluator returns before loading policy even though docs and health registration treat the plugin as enabled.",
      "review_followup": "Draft protected policy/runtime work needs maintainer architecture and security review after the narrow enablement blocker is fixed.",
